    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\n**Root cause:** Classic off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.\n\n```typescript\n// ❌ BUGGY — stops before the last element\nfor (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {\n\n// ✅ FIXED — iterates through all elements\nfor (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {\n```\n\nThe condition `items.length - 1` means the loop runs for indices `0` through `n-2`, permanently skipping index `n-1` (the last item). For a single-element array, `0 < 0` is immediately false so nothing is processed at all.\n\n**One-line change** in `src/utils.ts`. After the fix, all 6 tests in `tests/utils.test.ts` should pass (run with `npm test`).",
